Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Conan Episode 1016 "The \NMonorail Sniper Case (Part One)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[ED]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[OP]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[Eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.64,0:00:44.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.71,0:00:47.31,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What happened? Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.71,0:00:50.02,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,It hurts... It hurts...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.02,0:00:51.52,DCMain,MAN,0000,0000,0000,,Am I going to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.04,0:00:54.86,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You'll be fine, as long as \Nwe can stop the bleeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.20,0:00:56.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.62,0:01:04.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, could I borrow your scarf?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.32,0:01:06.29,DCMain,WOMAN,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.96,0:01:11.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, should we press \Nthe emergency stop button?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.03,0:01:13.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.44,0:01:30.68,DCItalic,RADIO,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter? Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.68,0:01:31.82,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Someone's injured.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.41,0:01:34.09,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,A passenger has been wounded.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.09,0:01:36.30,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Call the police and an ambulance.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.10,0:01:39.17,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry it up! Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.17,0:01:40.45,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.60,0:01:52.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A journey of a thousand miles \Nstarts with the first step!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:54.59,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Solve 1,000 mysteries and enter a new world!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.59,0:01:56.54,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Bullets fly into a moving train!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.54,0:01:58.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Track down the sniper who disappeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:00.43,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.43,0:02:02.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.18,0:02:05.02,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.99,0:03:52.00,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}The Monorail Sniper Case \N(Part One)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.40,0:03:49.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"The Monorail Sniper Case, Part One!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.12,0:04:06.20,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Is everyone all right? \NWhere's the injured person?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.20,0:04:10.14,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're fine. We stopped the \Nbleeding. He's sitting inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.53,0:04:13.66,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, let's find the culprit quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.66,0:04:14.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to tell me twice.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.10,0:04:18.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops. Preserving the crime \Nscene is our top priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.04,0:04:21.46,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't touch anything until \Nthe police arrive. Got it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.46,0:04:22.61,DCMain,EMPLOYEE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.42,0:04:29.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Where did the shot come from? \NWhich way is the wind blowing?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.88,0:04:33.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This way!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.07,0:04:34.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.05,0:04:38.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? There's been a shooting \Nnear the end of the monorail line.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.09,0:04:42.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you close the roads immediately, we can \Ntrap the culprit on the artificial island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.70,0:04:45.60,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, do it. I'll track down the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.91,0:04:53.73,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Megure, you heard him. \NWhat should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.96,0:05:00.45,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Instruct the monorail \Ncompany to stop service.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.45,0:05:05.23,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,Contact the Wangan Police Station \Nand have them set up checkpoints
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.23,0:05:07.11,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,at all Wangan-Toto Station exits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.11,0:05:16.62,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Toto Artificial Island
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.66,0:05:11.94,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll also set up checkpoints on all nine \Nbridges surrounding the artificial island.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.94,0:05:15.80,DCMain,MEGURE,0000,0000,0000,,We'll seal off the entire \Nisland and trap the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.80,0:05:16.62,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.70,0:05:41.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The moment the shot was fired, the monorail \Nwas around that spot on the rail.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.13,0:05:51.45,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet entered through the \Nsecond window from the front
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.22,0:05:57.56,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and struck the victim's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.14,0:05:59.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If we can determine the angle \Nof the hole in the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.96,0:06:00.75,Direction,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Direction of Travel
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.00,0:06:02.96,Victim,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Shooting Victim
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:02.96,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,the location of the shooting victim,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.96,0:06:07.97,Location,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Shooter's Location
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.50,0:06:07.59,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the monorail's location at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.19,0:06:11.96,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,then we can calculate where \Nthe shot was fired from.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.73,0:06:22.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shooter's location was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.24,0:06:27.68,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's that building.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:31.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.76,0:06:34.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.16,0:06:39.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? Uh, my daily horoscope said \Nmy guesses would be right today.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.78,0:06:42.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Your horoscope, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.39,0:06:44.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:48.80,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Who would believe that nonsense?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.26,0:06:54.14,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, look! I saw someone who \Nmight be the culprit over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.14,0:06:55.99,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.99,0:06:58.44,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,All right, kid! Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.10,0:07:05.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, Mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.08,0:07:13.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, it's an emergency.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.58,0:07:15.12,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Could you open the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.12,0:07:21.25,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the height of the monorail \Ncar, the shot was probably fired from...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.92,0:07:29.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, the fifth floor. The second \Nwindow from the end was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.37,0:07:30.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.16,0:07:35.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I was watching from \Ninside the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.18,0:08:00.22,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.93,0:08:23.51,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.77,0:08:25.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.04,0:08:40.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,This place is empty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.77,0:08:42.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no sign of the shooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:48.13,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe you made a mistake when \Nyou thought you saw the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.13,0:08:51.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That wasn't a mistake, it was a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.62,0:09:28.99,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.50,0:09:31.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The shot was definitely fired from here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:44.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like a man lives alone here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.30,0:09:46.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, could you thoroughly \Nsearch this apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.80,0:09:48.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to look around outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.71,0:09:50.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.62,0:09:52.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're already unlawfully entering.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.91,0:09:53.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.44,0:09:57.82,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, this is Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.30,0:09:59.70,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:01.97,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We've arrived at the monorail.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:04.70,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Forensics is currently \Nexamining the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.01,0:10:10.58,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Also, as you suggested, we've \Nblocked off all the roads.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.58,0:10:10.58,Checkpoint,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Checkpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.58,0:10:14.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Have you figured out anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.77,0:10:17.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it's about the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.89,0:10:21.25,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}His name is Maruta Daisuke-san, 28 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.93,0:10:22.39,Daisuke,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Maruta Daisuke (28)
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.25,0:10:23.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}He works for a construction company.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.89,0:10:27.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He was shot in the upper left arm, \Nand he's in no danger of dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.16,0:10:31.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet has been extracted, \Nand he's currently resting.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.17,0:10:35.96,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,He apparently doesn't know \Nanyone who owns a gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.96,0:10:38.86,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,nor has he done anything to \Nincur someone's ill will.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.28,0:10:42.20,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But that's all according to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.20,0:10:44.64,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We'll continue with our investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.64,0:10:45.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.73,0:10:48.87,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll contact you right away \Nif I find the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.48,0:10:57.76,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're faint,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.02,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but there are scuff marks left by something \Nheavy that was dragged down the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.18,0:11:11.08,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Conan-kun? What—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.08,0:11:12.62,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's me. Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.62,0:11:16.72,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, why are you calling \Nfrom Conan-kun's phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.72,0:11:19.65,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.65,0:11:21.72,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.72,0:11:24.30,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Then is there something \Nyou forgot to mention?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.30,0:11:26.89,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.89,0:11:30.66,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously? He must've been talking \Nto the old man until a moment ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.86,0:11:34.67,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, there's a location I'd like \Nforensics to examine immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.37,0:11:39.04,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.62,0:11:43.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.01,0:11:45.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.47,0:11:49.98,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go. Standing around here \Nis just a waste of our time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.48,0:11:57.61,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.46,0:12:03.44,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.22,0:12:05.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.64,0:12:07.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think this is?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.70,0:12:09.75,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Bloodstains.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.98,0:12:12.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They lead that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.40,0:12:15.52,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.52,0:12:19.20,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the culprit \Nis over there. Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.20,0:12:20.26,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.72,0:12:24.49,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.56,0:12:27.56,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's the problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.56,0:12:31.76,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Conan. We're pursuing a shooter, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.59,0:12:37.11,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Do the bloodstains have anything \Nto do with the shooter?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.46,0:12:39.06,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.61,0:12:46.62,Checkpoint2,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Checkpoint
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.63,0:12:49.63,Stop,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Please Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.25,0:13:00.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.02,0:13:01.88,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:04.19,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san, you were right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.19,0:13:05.76,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive as always, Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.00,0:13:08.64,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I was right? About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.90,0:13:10.14,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.48,0:13:12.89,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm talking about room 505.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.19,0:13:17.15,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As you suspected, we found gunshot residue.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.44,0:13:18.81,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.81,0:13:22.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Then the shot was fired from that room?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.44,0:13:25.28,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but that's not all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.48,0:13:31.16,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,We also observed a luminol \Nreaction on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.12,0:13:33.29,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.28,0:13:39.41,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,The bloodstains were apparently wiped \Naway after splattering on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.41,0:13:41.80,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Judging by the volume,\Nthe victim was probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.09,0:13:44.05,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The scuff marks in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.36,0:13:46.32,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The scrap of plastic sheet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:49.55,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet that was fired, and \Nthe bloodstains in the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.33,0:13:56.02,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean your shot \Nin the dark was right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.02,0:13:58.39,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.39,0:13:59.54,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:01.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.62,0:14:06.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I wonder if it was a coincidence that \Nthere were bloodstains in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.29,0:14:07.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Coincidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:09.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Shot in the dark?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.05,0:14:10.94,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,The bullet!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.63,0:14:15.58,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Takagi, have you figured out anything \Nfrom the bullet that was fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.74,0:14:22.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, forensics examined the bullet extracted \Nfrom the victim's upper left arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:30.28,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's a 30-caliber 7.62 millimeter full \Nmetal jacket Mauser military bullet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.79,0:14:32.60,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,also known as a Tokarev bullet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.94,0:14:36.73,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,You can snipe someone with a \NTokarev from that distance?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.86,0:14:37.84,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.84,0:14:43.48,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,but it's hard to imagine the culprit \Nused a handgun to snipe the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.08,0:14:49.74,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Which means the victim was coincidentally \Nstruck by a stray bullet?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.92,0:14:53.24,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it does seem that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.24,0:14:56.04,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Based on current evidence, the \Nculprit shot someone in room 505,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:15:03.00,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and the bullet passed through them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.51,0:15:07.32,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That bullet flew outside the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.81,0:15:12.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,pierced the monorail window, \Nand struck the victim's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.73,0:15:17.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Is that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.77,0:15:20.77,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,There's a hundred meters between \Nthe window and the monorail line.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.04,0:15:27.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It passed through a person's body, pierced \Na monorail window, and struck someone's arm.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.53,0:15:28.78,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.08,0:15:33.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Tokarevs are designed to \Nhave excellent penetration.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.26,0:15:35.78,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It was a handgun and not a rifle?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.32,0:15:39.08,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Handguns and rifles have \Ndifferent trajectories,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:42.54,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,but striking the first victim must have \Napplied an angle to the bullet's path.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.97,0:15:44.79,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But that would mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.25,0:15:50.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible to do intentionally, but \Nwith the right series of coincidences...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.83,0:15:53.30,DCItalic,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.79,0:15:56.63,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, that's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.13,0:15:59.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.24,0:16:03.31,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We found the connection between \Nthe culprit and the bloodstains.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.38,0:16:16.07,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.59,0:16:17.92,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Over here, Mister.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.26,0:16:24.16,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We can follow these bloodstains all we want,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.16,0:16:27.45,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but won't the culprit escape \Nwhile we're wasting time here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.45,0:16:29.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's this smell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.60,0:16:56.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, there's a woman tied up in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.54,0:16:58.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This smell...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.61,0:17:20.89,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mister, it's gasoline!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.80,0:17:29.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it. The door is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.62,0:17:31.92,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have to break the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.73,0:17:38.83,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.00,0:17:47.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Run, mister!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.56,0:18:22.61,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Mori-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.41,0:18:24.84,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:25.79,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Are you hurt?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.22,0:18:27.91,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,We're fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.22,0:18:30.92,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Did that woman say anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.92,0:18:32.03,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:34.34,Tamura,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(250,460)}Tamura Kiyomi (32)
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.03,0:18:34.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}She was rather frightened and distraught,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.16,0:18:37.42,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,but she said while walking around this area,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:40.07,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,something was suddenly \Nplaced against her mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.43,0:18:42.24,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,and she lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.79,0:18:46.06,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,When she woke up after the attack,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.06,0:18:49.25,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,she'd been abandoned inside the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.25,0:18:52.71,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Does she know who may have \Nwanted to kidnap her?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.71,0:18:54.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,She has no idea who it could've been.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.66,0:19:00.74,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, we've confirmed the \Nvictim's background and questioned her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.74,0:19:06.52,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,We didn't find anything in her background or \Ntestimony that would lead us to the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.52,0:19:08.39,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.39,0:19:10.52,DCMain,POLICE,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.77,0:19:13.59,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,No clues, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.17,0:19:19.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, the culprit must have rather \Nviolent tendencies to set fire to a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.13,0:19:23.80,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They've probably been watching \Nus tracking them down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.52,0:19:27.48,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,They did this to disrupt the investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.16,0:19:31.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,So, have there been any \Ndevelopments with the apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.71,0:19:34.81,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,As you suspected, they seem to \Nhave wrapped the victim in a sheet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:37.23,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,and are transporting them somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.38,0:19:43.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Detective Takagi, why is the culprit \Ntaking the victim away from the apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.37,0:19:44.66,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.82,0:19:47.83,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,They're obviously trying \Nto hide the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.03,0:19:55.03,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think carrying the victim \Naround with them is too risky?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.03,0:19:57.09,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.57,0:20:02.09,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps there's a reason \Nthey have to take that risk.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.52,0:20:05.26,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you were the culprit, what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.69,0:20:06.43,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.43,0:20:10.90,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,Well, normally you'd want to get rid \Nof the victim as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.90,0:20:12.62,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,But you're still carrying them with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.62,0:20:13.77,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where would you take them?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.77,0:20:15.99,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.56,0:20:20.23,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If you carried something as large \Nas a body through a normal place,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.23,0:20:22.27,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,you'd draw attention to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.27,0:20:26.82,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Where would it seem natural to \Ncarry something large around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:30.95,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. That place would work.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.32,0:20:32.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.38,0:20:34.69,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,There's only one place \Non this artificial island
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.69,0:20:37.74,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,where it wouldn't seem unnatural \Nto carry something large.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:42.20,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,It matches the direction indicated \Nby the trail of blood, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.20,0:20:49.90,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Toto Market, Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.96,0:21:31.12,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,You certainly wouldn't \Nstand out at Toto Market
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.12,0:21:34.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,by carrying something large and heavy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.27,0:21:36.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,like a tuna or amberjack.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.44,0:21:40.27,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,But what is the culprit trying \Nto accomplish by doing that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.64,0:21:45.28,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't determining that and \Ncatching the culprit our job?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.13,0:22:10.55,TotoMarket,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Toto Market
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.08,0:22:23.08,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit should be somewhere in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.94,0:24:08.96,DCEpPreview,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Episode Preview
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.33,0:23:47.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What did the culprit come here to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.25,0:23:50.40,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,This place is pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.40,0:23:52.32,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's big and deserted.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.07,0:23:56.08,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,It's the perfect place to hide a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.46,0:23:57.93,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,We're playing hide-and-seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.08,0:24:02.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Are they hiding somewhere, or...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.20,0:24:06.59,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you stop playing dumb?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.96,0:24:14.97,DCNextEp,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,The Monorail Sniper Case \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.42,0:24:14.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The next episode of Conan is "The \NMonorail Sniper Case, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.98,0:24:34.91,Hint,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Turret Truck
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.12,0:24:33.29,DCMain,GENTA,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan's hint! My first in a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.29,0:24:34.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,A turret truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:37.66,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Hey, that's a tuna! Stop that turret truck!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.91,0:24:39.91,Don'tMiss,TEXT,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the next episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.66,0:24:38.49,DCMain,TAKAGI,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.49,0:24:39.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}Just ignore them.
